00:00.000 --> 00:05.000
What are the documents for the operation?

00:05.000 --> 00:11.000
All economic operations are documented in accordance with the current legislation.

00:11.000 --> 00:19.000
This documentation is taken to the accountants of the enterprises and is reflected in the accounting record.

00:19.000 --> 00:29.000
The variety of existing documents can be grouped according to certain characteristics.

00:29.000 --> 00:38.000
The purpose of the documents can be administrative, combined, accounting and justification.

00:38.000 --> 00:48.000
The example of administrative documents is the order of the manager or the contract of the organization, for example, the delivery contract.

00:48.000 --> 00:57.000
Combined documents are payment and accounting information when accounting with the staff.

00:57.000 --> 01:02.000
Accounting documents are the accounting certificate.

01:02.000 --> 01:08.000
Justification documents are the deposit for the purchase of a product.

01:08.000 --> 01:14.000
The time of the documents' completion can be primary or combined.

01:14.000 --> 01:24.000
The primary documents are the payment and accounting documents.

01:24.000 --> 01:32.000
The combined documents are the register of all payment and accounting documents for one day.

01:32.000 --> 01:40.000
The documents on the volume of information are divided into disposable and accumulative.

01:40.000 --> 01:45.000
The documents on the place of composition are external and internal.

01:45.000 --> 01:53.000
For example, the external document is the deposit from the supplier, the internal document is the incoming order of the organization.

01:53.000 --> 02:01.000
The documents can look like a table, questionnaire and combined.

02:01.000 --> 02:10.000
It is better to design and design primary documents with the managers in close contact with the accounting department.

02:10.000 --> 02:15.000
This will prevent unnecessary errors when designing documents.

02:15.000 --> 02:27.000
Any organization should select those who have a direct relationship with the design of primary documents and train them to design them correctly.

02:27.000 --> 02:35.000
It is important to remember that the period of storing primary documents is regulated in Russia for at least 5 years.

02:35.000 --> 02:42.000
The responsibility for storing and filling them is not the accountant, but the manager.

02:42.000 --> 02:50.000
All economic operations should be designed with justification documents.

02:50.000 --> 02:58.000
These documents are the primary accounting documents, on the basis of which accounting is carried out.

02:58.000 --> 03:08.000
The internal documents are the requirements, the incoming order, the external documents, the accounts, the deposits.

03:08.000 --> 03:16.000
The documents can be multilateral, such as a trilateral contract or a multilateral act.

03:17.000 --> 03:25.000
A specific document should be created for each economic operation.

03:25.000 --> 03:32.000
For example, I would like to draw your attention to the combined table in different situations.

03:32.000 --> 03:36.000
Let's say that the primary funds are reflected as a contribution to the statutory capital.

03:36.000 --> 03:38.000
What documents are required for this?

03:39.000 --> 03:46.000
The primary funds received from the institutions are the ones that are used to produce the documents.

03:46.000 --> 03:52.000
The primary funds are received on the basis of the Act on the Receipt and Transmission of Primary Funds.

03:52.000 --> 03:58.000
The procedure for acquiring the primary funds also consists of several stages.

03:58.000 --> 04:05.000
First, a purchase-sale contract is drawn up, and a bill for payment is issued.

04:05.000 --> 04:07.000
This is also a type of document.

04:07.000 --> 04:13.000
The main funds are paid by the legal entities.

04:13.000 --> 04:18.000
This means that the account will be issued and the organization will be charged.

04:18.000 --> 04:26.000
To obtain the primary funds, the goods-transport deposit is issued and the invoice is accompanied by it.

04:26.000 --> 04:32.000
The main funds of the accounting are taken into account.

04:32.000 --> 04:38.000
The document is drawn up as the Act on the Receipt and Transmission of Primary Funds.

04:38.000 --> 04:43.000
The primary funds are transferred to the current long-term lease.

04:43.000 --> 04:48.000
The lease contract is drawn up and the payment is issued.

04:48.000 --> 04:55.000
To record the fact of the transfer of the primary funds to the leaseholder,

04:55.000 --> 04:59.000
the Act on the Receipt and Transmission of Primary Funds is drawn up.

04:59.000 --> 05:05.000
The payment is recorded by the organization's account.

05:05.000 --> 05:11.000
This is an example of the documentation of some operations.

05:11.000 --> 05:21.000
The justification documents of the organization confirm the fact of the economic operation.

05:22.000 --> 05:31.000
The justification documents can be used for the income and expenditure deposits, various documents, cash checks, and other documents.

05:31.000 --> 05:39.000
The accounting staff usually deal with accounting documents.

05:39.000 --> 05:45.000
These documents do not contain facts that confirm the performance of economic operations.

05:45.000 --> 05:52.000
These are the accounts of the accountant, the accounting documents,

05:52.000 --> 05:57.000
and they serve as the basis for further accounting records.

05:57.000 --> 06:02.000
The accounting registers are the documents of analytical and synthetic accounting,

06:02.000 --> 06:05.000
the notations, the order books, and the accounting books,

06:05.000 --> 06:09.000
but they are not the subject of our consideration in this course.

06:09.000 --> 06:17.000
The combined documents contain the signs of both the administrative and the justification documents.

06:17.000 --> 06:24.000
For example, the deposit requirement for the release of materials from warehouses,

06:24.000 --> 06:29.000
the production of goods, the transport deposit, the accounting payment,

06:29.000 --> 06:32.000
the notice of payment, the salary, and so on.

06:33.000 --> 06:40.000
I will try to explain to you what the combined documents are.

06:40.000 --> 06:45.000
Let's take the accounting payment notice for the payment of the salary.

06:45.000 --> 06:51.000
The first function of the document is the accounting registration document.

06:51.000 --> 06:58.000
The accountant compiles this notice for the persons receiving the salary,

06:58.000 --> 07:05.000
then he lists the salary and determines the amount to be paid.

07:05.000 --> 07:09.000
Then the function of this document is the administrative one.

07:09.000 --> 07:14.000
After the accounting payment notice is transferred to the cash register,

07:14.000 --> 07:19.000
it serves as the basis for issuing the salary to each worker.

07:19.000 --> 07:29.000
After the salary is issued, all workers are signed that they have received the money.

07:29.000 --> 07:36.000
This is the justification document for the cash register that he has issued the money from the cash register.

07:36.000 --> 07:47.000
The primary documents are the documents for the payment and release of materials,

07:47.000 --> 07:53.000
the payment of the salary, the unloading of products, the cash register, the payment instructions, and so on.

07:53.000 --> 07:58.000
The combined documents are the first stage of the data collection,

07:58.000 --> 08:04.000
which is contained in several primary documents that precede their accounting processing.

08:04.000 --> 08:09.000
For example, these are the goods reports of the materially responsible persons,

08:09.000 --> 08:18.000
cash register reports, or reports of the persons responsible for the expenditure of the money advance.

08:18.000 --> 08:22.000
This is how the primary documents are summarized,

08:22.000 --> 08:26.000
and the payment instructions are also calculated according to the salary.

08:26.000 --> 08:34.000
The documents on which the economic operations have been carried out are sent to your accountant,

08:34.000 --> 08:37.000
where three types of verification are carried out.

08:37.000 --> 08:45.000
The first type is a formal verification, when the accountant checks the correctness of the form.

08:45.000 --> 08:50.000
Are all the sections of the document filled in?

08:50.000 --> 08:54.000
Are all the requisites filled in correctly?

08:54.000 --> 08:56.000
Are the requisites fully filled in?

08:56.000 --> 09:00.000
The second type is a verification of the existence of the document.

09:00.000 --> 09:08.000
This is a verification of the existence of the document.

09:08.000 --> 09:11.000
And finally, the third type is an arithmetic verification,

09:11.000 --> 09:15.000
which checks the correctness of the calculation of the data in the document.

09:15.000 --> 09:24.000
The accountant must calculate whether all the data is filled in correctly.

09:25.000 --> 09:30.000
What should be done to avoid mistakes?

09:30.000 --> 09:36.000
The head of the organization must build a scheme of the circulation of the document.

09:36.000 --> 09:40.000
He must identify the persons who make up the document,

09:40.000 --> 09:45.000
who check it, and who, based on the document,

09:45.000 --> 09:53.000
either issue the goods, or receive the goods, or sum up the work done.

09:53.000 --> 09:56.000
He must conduct an analysis of the typical errors,

09:56.000 --> 09:59.000
and teach everyone who has a relationship with the registration of the document

09:59.000 --> 10:02.000
the basic rules of registration.

10:02.000 --> 10:05.000
He must organize the service of internal control.

10:05.000 --> 10:10.000
The modern and high-quality registration of primary accounting documents,

10:10.000 --> 10:14.000
their transfer to the established terms for reflection in the accounting record,

10:14.000 --> 10:17.000
as well as the reliability of the data contained in them,

10:17.000 --> 10:23.000
provide the persons who have compiled and signed these documents.

10:23.000 --> 10:29.000
An example of a circulation scheme is shown in the textbook.

10:29.000 --> 10:33.000
Here is a video lecture in the form of a table.

10:33.000 --> 10:39.000
For example, to issue a travel list to a driver,

10:39.000 --> 10:43.000
this document must be compiled by either the dispatcher,

10:43.000 --> 10:46.000
or the mechanic, or the driver himself.

10:46.000 --> 10:53.000
The period for which this document is compiled is the period of the trip.

10:53.000 --> 10:59.000
The organization's employees must compile this document every day.

10:59.000 --> 11:02.000
Who will process the document?

11:02.000 --> 11:07.000
The person in charge is appointed, the accountant,

11:07.000 --> 11:10.000
and these documents are processed every day.

11:10.000 --> 11:13.000
When the document is transferred to the archive,

11:13.000 --> 11:16.000
the person in charge is also assigned,

11:16.000 --> 11:19.000
who must hand this document over to the archive,

11:19.000 --> 11:21.000
and the transfer period to the archive,

11:21.000 --> 11:24.000
let's say, the period of the report.

11:24.000 --> 11:29.000
The accountant collects the travel lists within a month,

11:29.000 --> 11:33.000
and at the end, he submits them to the archive.

